      "about.seat.s2.m1": "Industry deployment",
      "about.seat.s2.m2": "Regulatory authority",
      "about.seat.s3.title": "Capital<br/>& technology",
      "about.seat.s3.m1": "Capital discipline",
      "about.seat.s3.m2": "Platform strategy",
      "careers.princ.p1.h3": "Engineering judgment first.",
      "careers.princ.p1.body": "The discipline that owns the work owns the decision. Engineers run engineering. Software runs software. Neither overrides the other on the other's domain. Disagreements are resolved by talking to the person with the regulatory authority.",
      "careers.princ.p2.h3": "Quality over velocity.",
      "careers.princ.p2.body": "The platform produces work that humans sign and clients pay for. We move at the speed of getting it right, not at the speed of demos. Shipped code is reviewed by engineers, not by sprint cadence.",
      "careers.princ.p3.h3": "Small, senior, long-running teams.",
      "careers.princ.p3.body": "We hire experienced people, give them ownership, and keep teams small enough that everyone can hold the whole system in their head. Permanence over rotation. Depth over breadth of org chart.",
      "careers.princ.p4.h3": "Open formats. No proprietary lock.",
      "careers.princ.p4.body": "Builtly itself is built on open standards: IFC4, BCF, GeoJSON, Eurocode logic. The same applies internally — documents, infrastructure, communication. Nothing locked behind one vendor or one person.",
      "careers.princ.p5.h3": "Remote first. Deliberate in-person.",
      "careers.princ.p5.body": "The work is digital. The team is distributed. We meet in person several times per year for the kind of work that benefits from a whiteboard and a long table. The rest of the time, we work where we work best.",
