      "contact.q.h3": "The actual question.",
      "contact.sit.h3": "Your situation.",
      "contact.tl.h3": "The timeline.",
      "contact.fmt.h3": "The format.",
      "contact.fact.corp.h": "Corporate identity.",
      "contact.fact.ops.h": "Operating facts.",
      "contact.fact.howWork.h": "How we work.",
      "contact.h3body.commercial.p": "The primary commercial conversation. Consultancies evaluating Builtly for full-platform deployment, multi-discipline coverage and seat-based licensing. Developers, lenders and asset managers buying per-deliverable. Procurement teams running formal vendor onboarding.",
      "contact.h3body.commercial.body": "After the introductory call: a tailored demo against your actual disciplines, a pilot proposal where relevant, and commercial terms documented for procurement review. Conversations typically run two to six weeks from first contact to signed agreement.",
      "contact.h3body.integration.p": "API access, white-label arrangements and embedded integrations. Used by proptech platforms, lender systems, consultancy networks and partners who want to surface Builtly capabilities inside their own products. Volume pricing and SLA negotiated case-by-case.",
      "contact.h3body.integration.body": "Conversations typically run six to twelve weeks from first contact to technical integration kickoff. Volume commitment and integration depth determine commercial terms.",
      "contact.h3body.media.p": "For interview requests, analyst briefings, fact-checking, market commentary and access to the media kit. Same-week response on timed requests for journalists working on a deadline.",
      "contact.h3body.media.body": "The media kit covers the logo files, company facts, founder photos and a brief background document. Available on request rather than via public download.",
      "contact.h3body.hiring.p": "For applications against open positions and for general expressions of interest where no role currently advertises. Senior referrals welcomed.",
      "contact.h3body.hiring.body": "Every application gets a response within five business days, either to advance to a conversation or to confirm receipt and timeline for review.",
      "contact.q.p": "What do you need from us? A demo? A licence quote? Information for a story? An integration discussion? The first paragraph should clarify the request.",
      "contact.sit.p": "What is the firm, the role, the project, or the publication? We do not need a full backgrounder — two or three lines is enough to calibrate the response.",
      "contact.tl.p": "When do you need a response, and when do you need a decision or output? Hard deadlines get prioritised. Inquiries with no urgency get the same care but a longer queue.",
      "contact.fmt.p": "If you prefer a written response, a 30-minute call, or a longer briefing, say so. The default is a written reply with a proposed next step.",
