      "ind.consult.h4": "Modules used by consultancies",
      "ind.uc.acq.h4": "Site acquisition under timeline pressure.",
      "ind.uc.lend.h4": "Construction-loan underwriting at portfolio scale.",
      "ind.uc.climate.h4": "Portfolio climate-risk disclosure.",
      "ind.uc.vel.h4": "Consultancy delivery velocity.",
      "ind.uc.tender.h4": "Public tender preparation under capacity constraint.",
      "ind.consult.p1": "Engineering consultancies are the primary customer for everything Builtly does. The platform was designed from the inside of the practice — by engineers who have produced these deliverables under regulatory authority — and is deployed seat-based across multi-discipline teams.",
      "ind.consult.p2": "The result for the consultancy: faster deliveries, more projects per senior, better margin per delivery, and senior capacity finally directed at the work that requires senior judgement.",
      "ind.dev.p1": "Builtly turns multi-week reports into same-day deliverables. For complex sites the developer still engages a consultancy — Builtly does not replace that — but feasibility, acquisition due diligence and screening run in hours instead of weeks.",
      "ind.lend.p1": "The platform produces structured outputs that integrate into credit-decisioning systems and portfolio-monitoring dashboards. White-label and API delivery available alongside the direct portal.",
      "ind.asset.p1": "The platform scales across thousands of assets without scaling expert capacity. Results are auditable and structured for downstream investor reporting, regulatory disclosure and asset-level operational decisions.",
      "ind.public.p1": "Typical engagement runs through a consultancy partner that holds the public-sector contract, with Builtly as the underlying production layer. Direct engagement available for agencies that procure platform tooling directly.",
      "ind.uc.acq.scenario": "A developer is bidding on a site with a one-week exclusivity window. The traditional path requires a two-week consultancy feasibility — too slow. Builtly produces a regulatory-grade feasibility study from the cadastral and planning data overnight.",
      "ind.uc.acq.result": "From weeks to same-day. Decision moves from inference to evidence before exclusivity expires.",
      "ind.uc.lend.scenario": "A lender originates hundreds of construction loans per year. Manual technical review per loan is prohibitive, but skipping it surfaces risk only at default. Builtly produces a technical-credit basis document per loan automatically, with engineer review on flagged exceptions.",
      "ind.uc.lend.result": "Volume that was uneconomic to review manually becomes routine. Risk surfaces earlier in the lending cycle.",
      "ind.uc.climate.scenario": "A real-estate fund manager is required to disclose climate-risk exposure across portfolio assets under financial-sector climate-disclosure rules. Manual assessment of thousands of assets is infeasible. Builtly produces per-asset climate-risk reports automatically and aggregates to portfolio level.",
      "ind.uc.climate.result": "Portfolio-scale compliance without portfolio-scale consultancy fees. Audit trail intact for regulatory examination.",
      "ind.uc.vel.scenario": "A consultancy's geotechnical team has 15 small-to-medium projects in queue, all requiring a similar baseline assessment plus project-specific judgement. Senior engineers should be doing the judgement, not the baseline.",
      "ind.uc.vel.result": "Senior engineer time spent on engineering judgement, not on report formatting. Throughput increases without staffing expansion.",
      "ind.uc.tender.scenario": "A public infrastructure agency has more tender packages to review than internal engineering capacity allows. Builtly produces the technical evaluation per submission, with senior engineers reviewing the platform output rather than producing it from scratch.",
      "ind.uc.tender.result": "Engineering bottleneck inside the agency is unlocked. Procurement cadence accelerates without compromising review quality.",
      "ind.eng.lic.p1": "The primary engagement model. A consultancy licenses the full platform for use across its engineering teams, with seat-based access and per-deliverable commercial terms layered on top. Annual commitment with discipline coverage tailored to the firm.",
      "ind.eng.lic.p2": "Suitable for consultancies with regular deliverable volume across multiple disciplines. The most economic route at scale.",
      "ind.eng.dir.p1": "Per-deliverable purchase directly from the portal. The buyer uploads project inputs, selects the module and delivery tier, and receives the deliverable on payment. No platform commitment required.",
      "ind.eng.dir.p2": "Suitable for developers, lenders and asset managers buying automated-tier deliverables on demand. Engineer-reviewed and attested tiers also available per-deliverable.",
      "ind.eng.partner.p1": "API integration or white-label arrangement for partners that embed Builtly capabilities in their own offering — proptech platforms, lender systems, real-estate platforms and consultancy networks. Volume pricing, dedicated SLAs and joint deployment support.",
      "ind.eng.partner.p2": "Suitable for high-volume integrations and where the platform's outputs are inputs to a broader workflow.",
