      "trust.p.termination": "On contract termination the customer retains the right to export everything. Builtly retains operational logs and audit trails for the period required by the customer's regulatory environment, and deletes the rest under documented procedure.",
      "trust.p.training": "Customers who actively want their de-identified data to contribute to model improvement may opt in under a separate addendum — but the default is no training, no exception.",
      "trust.p.residency": "For customers with disclosure obligations under climate, financial or public-procurement rules, the residency configuration becomes part of the regulatory examination record — and is documented accordingly.",
      "trust.p.sessions": "Session management follows enterprise norms: configurable session length, forced re-authentication for sensitive operations, and full session logging available for security operations review.",
      "trust.p.signing": "Signed deliverables carry SHA-256 cryptographic signatures bound to the platform version and the signing engineer's identity — making any post-signature modification cryptographically detectable.",
      "trust.p.inference": "AI inference is isolated per tenant: requests do not cross tenant boundaries, and model context is reset between requests. There is no shared inference state across customers.",
      "trust.p.audit": "For regulatory examination, the trail is the answer to \"how did this number get into this report?\" — without requiring reconstruction by the original engineering team.",
      "trust.p.signature": "The signature artefact travels with the document — the receiving party can verify integrity without depending on Builtly remaining operational. Open specification means independent verification is possible at any future date.",
      "trust.p.export": "The export is designed to be defensible: a third-party expert can examine the record, re-run the deterministic computations, and arrive at the same numbers — independent of any platform vendor.",
      "trust.p.rulepack": "Each module's output specifies the exact code version and rule-pack version applied — so the regulatory basis of every deliverable is unambiguous and reproducible at audit.",
      "trust.p.dpa": "A standard Data Processing Agreement is available for customers subject to GDPR or equivalent regional data-protection rules, and a Data Protection Officer is named in every active agreement.",
      "trust.p.pack": "The pack is intended to compress vendor-onboarding from weeks to days. For deeper diligence, additional materials are made available under standard NDA.",
