      "sec.bim.tag": "Project North · IFC4 · multi-block residential",
      "sec.bim.tagline": "What was once a model now becomes a basis for decisions.",
      "sec.engine.title": "The engine",
      "sec.engine.tag": "Mathematics behind the modules",
      "sec.algorithms.h2.l2": "layered algorithms.",
      "prob.p1.body": "Documentation and reporting consume 40–60% of an engineer's day — driven by stricter regulation, more complex documentation requirements and tool chains that have grown fragmented over twenty years. Builtly is for engineers who want to spend more time on the actual engineering.",
      "prob.p2.body": "AI, geometry processing and distributed compute have matured over the past five years to the point where compliance-grade engineering software is actually possible — not as an integration layer between existing tools, but as one coherent portal. Builtly is for engineers who want to use that mature technology now.",
      "prob.p3.body": "Markets globally lack senior structural, geotechnical, fire and acoustical engineers. Automating routine production frees expert capacity for work that genuinely requires professional judgment — where human accountability cannot be replaced.",
      "prob.p4.body": "Drawings in CAD. Calculations in spreadsheets. Reports in word processors. Requirements in separate sources. Every handoff is manual — and every manual handoff is a coordination problem, a delay, and a risk.",
      "about.intro.l1": "It is not coincidental. It is the prerequisite.",
      "about.strong.preserved": "What is not preserved is the assumption that the only way to ship a signed deliverable is to do every step by hand.",
      "about.strong.result": "Builtly is the tool for engineers who want to use that maturity now.",
      "about.strong.operational": "The platform is operational. The portal is live. The principles are not negotiable.",
      "about.h2.engineer": "The engineer provides the engineering.",
